post_text: Peñasco ISD is working with Kit Carson Telecom to help provide Internet access to district families who currently lack it. Those families will be contacted by Kit Carson in the next few days. If you indicated you did not have Internet on the re-entry survey before the start of school or told a teacher or counselor that you do not have Internet, then you are on the list given to Kit Carson. If you think the district might not know about your Internet issues or have your current phone number, please contact Community Schools Coordinator Michael Noll: mnoll@penascoisd.com, 575-779-1466.

post_text: Access to Internet is required for many day-to-day activities and is more important than ever now that schools across New Mexico and the country are meeting online. To get a better picture of cell phone Internet availability in the Peñasco area (including, but not limited to, the following communities: Peñasco, Rio Lucio, Vadito, Rodarte, Llano, Chamisal, El Valle, Trampas, Ojo Sarco, Truchas, and Dixon), Peñasco ISD is collecting info about wireless carriers, plans, and coverage. Info collected through this form will help the district communicate the needs of area residents to wireless companies and organizations focused on rural connectivity. Everyone living in the Peñasco area is encouraged to fill out the survey, not just families with children in the Peñasco schools. Link in the web page below.

CLASS OF 2020 GRADUATION - Saturday, June 27, 2020 @ 11:00 am. Unfortunately, due to the COVID-19 crisis, we are unable to host a large gathering and have the graduation ceremony to which we are all accustomed. Each graduate only has two passes to share with a limited number of family members.

All are invited to join our long-awaited celebration virtually to celebrate our Class of 2020!!
WE WILL BE LIVE-STREAMING THE GRADUATION CEREMONY ON OUR DISTRICT FACEBOOK PAGE ON SATURDAY, 6/27/2020 STARTING AT 11:00 AM.
WE WILL ALSO POST A VIDEO OF THE CEREMONY ON YOUTUBE LATER THAT DAY.

post_text:
2020 Senior Spotlight: STEFANI VIGIL

After returning to Peñasco High School, Stefani worked very hard to ensure she would graduate with her classmates. In her free time, she enjoys playing sports such as basketball, volleyball, and baseball. She also enjoys camping, four-wheeling, and spending time with friends and family. Stefani has shared that she’s enjoyed being a student at Penasco High School and is honored and grateful to be able to graduate with all of her classmates and friends with whom she grew up since Headstart. She plans to attend CNM in Albuquerque, NM this fall where she will pursue a degree in Business and Cosmetology. Stefani is the daughter of Kathy Baca and Fabian Vigil. We wish Stefani all the best in all of her future endeavors!

post_text:
2020 Senior Spotlight: JOSÉ “JJ” VELARDE

During his four years in high school, JJ was a key member of the Special Olympics team participating in Bowling and Track where he ran the 100 M and 200 M races. JJ was also involved in starting up a coffee cart for the school staff which included baked goods that he and his classmates baked. His interests include working on classic cars and trucks. After high school, JJ plans to go to the Santa Fe Community College and his long-term goal is to follow his interest to work on classic cars and trucks. JJ is the son of Cecilia and José Velarde. We wish JJ all the best in all of his future endeavors!

2020 Senior Spotlight: ALEXANDRIA SANDOVAL

Throughout her four years in high school, Alex participated in and was a vital team member of Volleyball, Basketball, Cross Country, and Track & Field. She is also a member of the National Honor Society- Jicarita Chapter. Alex has been a participant of our RISE Program taking courses at Northern New Mexico College in Española, NM and due to her hard work and dedication she will be receiving her Associate’s Degree this spring. 2020 Senior Spotlight: CYNTHIA MONTOYA

While in high school, Cynthia participated in Envirothon. She was a member of the basketball team her freshman year and she spent time volunteering at Watermelon Ranch. Cynthia participated in our RISE program attending college courses at Northern New Mexico College in Española. Her interests include drawing, music, watching anime, reading, playing video games, and hiking. After high school, Cynthia will be joining the US Air Force as a K-9 handler for a few years but would like to eventually become a drill sergeant. She also plans to work on earning her degree in Criminology to become a detective. Cynthia plans to serve in the military full time for 6 years and hopes to be based in either Japan or New York City. If she decides not to make the military a career she hopes to work in New York City as a detective. Cynthia is the daughter of Veronica and Robert Montoya. We wish Cynthia all the best in all of her future endeavors!

Throughout high school, Ariana was a vital member of the Basketball team, Volleyball team, Cross Country Team, and the Track & Field team. She was also on the Envirothon team and participated in 4-H. Ariana is the daughter of Anita and Marvin MacAuley. We wish Ariana all the best in all of her future endeavors!

2020 Senior Spotlight: JORDAN EGAN-HARRIS
While attending Peñasco High School, Jordan participated in our RISE program and will be receiving her AA from Northern New Mexico College this spring. She has enjoyed working at Starbucks and her interests include reading, writing, singing, and helping people. She plans to attend New Mexico State University after taking a semester off to save up some money and do some volunteering at the local animal shelter and some shadowing at a local hospital. Jordan plans to pursue a career in medicine. Jordan is the daughter of Deborah and Patrick Harris. We wish Jordan all the best in all of her future endeavors!

Chaske participated in our RISE program, taking college courses at Northern New Mexico College. His one major interest is fishing. Chaske has enlisted in the Air Force and has already taken his oath of enlistment. Chaske is the son of Elektra Badash and Hal Dyer. We wish Chaske all the best in all of his future endeavors!

2020 Senior Spotlight: ANGELINA ARCHULETA
During her four years of high school, Angelina was on the basketball team and was a member of the National Honor Society, Jicarita Chapter. She participated in our RISE program and worked very hard to receive her Associate’s degree in Psychology from Northern New Mexico College in May 2019 at the end of her junior year. Some of her interests are literature, music, and studying history. In the fall of 2020, Angelina will be attending New Mexico Highlands University in Las Vegas, NM where she plans to major in Psychology and minor in Political Science. Angelina is the daughter of Alice Gonzales and Antonio Archuleta. We wish Angelina all the best in all of her future endeavors!

post_text: On May 23rd, the originally planned date for Graduation, we will have our own "Be the Light" Celebration in honor of our Class of 2020. At 8:20 pm (20:20 military time) the lights in and around the school will be turned on and we invite the community to participate by turning on your porch lights, house lights, outdoor lights, and/or blue/yellow/white decorative holiday lights at 8:20 pm. The school campus will be opened up at 8:20 pm and we encourage our Seniors, their families, and the community to drive slowly & safely through the campus in celebration of our Class of 2020. The Gates will close at 9:00 pm.

Our efforts to provide breakfast and lunches to the children of our community has been acknowledge by Governor Michelle Lujan Grisham. She celebrated our team of staff and volunteers yesterday in her first ever "Good News" Facebook broadcast. Our Food Service Manager and the Fire Departments who are a key part of this effort are mentioned starting at minute 5:50.

https://www.facebook.com/GovMLG/videos/3197789833585480/

In addition she provided more praise in her twitter feed today for all staff featuring photos of our bus drivers, cooks ,and the abundance of lunch bags ready for distribution.

https://twitter.com/GovMLG/status/1258842558697893888

Governor Lujan Grisham called Shiela Rodriguez a rockstar. We think so too!

We are so honored to be acknowledged. Thanks to the team and thank you Governor Lujan Grisham.

Dear Peñasco Elementary School Families,

The time has come to register your child for the 2020-2021 school year. To do this most efficiently with the least amount of contact due to COVID-19, we have put the registration form online. To fill out the form, please go to:

https://forms.gle/TexZntZcRFEbdFXHA

Questions marked with a red star are required to continue while questions without the red star need to be only filled out if they apply to your situation. The registration should take about 15 minutes to complete. Once you have completed for one child, you will be given an option to fill out another form for additional children. We will need one completed form per child. If you cannot fill out the form online, please contact me so we can make other arrangements. Thank you for getting this done so we can get ready for the 2020-2021 school year!

All the best,

Aaron J. Mitchell
Elementary Principal and Special Education Director
Peñasco Independent Schools
(505) 692-4591 (Cell phone)
amitchell@penascoisd.com

post_text:
Hello all,

I hope this post finds everyone doing well.

Two times a week, I am inviting guest readers to join my preschool class for Story Time. Over the course of the year my students have been introduced to community helpers, and I think that there is no time like the present for our littlest of learners to feel community. Reading any story of your choice, you would record yourself reading a story (5 to 7 minutes), and I would post it to my google classroom for my students to view at home.

Teachers, if you have any students that need to bring up a grade or make up community service hours this could be an idea!

If anyone is interested, please email me at gtrujillo@penascoisd.com.

Thank you,
Mrs. Genevieve Trujillo

post_text:
Middle & High School Students,
On behalf of your teachers, counselor, and myself we are very proud of how you are stepping up and handling the situation we are all in. Most of you have really taken on the challenge of working from home and are making great gains. Some may be struggling to figure things out and to get going- Don't Give Up!! The only way you'll fail is if you do nothing and don't respond to teachers reaching out to you. We want all of you to pass but we need to hear from you and to make the effort to get the job done. We're almost there- only 5 weeks left of school. Get Going and Keep it Going!! Check your school gmail account daily and send your teachers emails when you need help. We are all here to help make the end of year a successful one.

Sincerely,
Marina B. Lopez
mlopez@penasco.k12.nm.us
575-779-1574

post_text:
New Behavioral Health Resource

The state of New Mexico has launched NMConnect, a new phone app that provides free 24-hour crisis and non-crisis support and access to behavioral health professionals who can text or talk via phone with individuals needing a listening ear or referrals to longer-term support. The app links users to the New Mexico Crisis Access Line (NMCAL), which provides safety net services statewide.

NMCAL is still available via phone 24/7 toll-free by calling 1-855-NMCRISIS (1-855-662-7474).

post_text:
Parents & Students, Please Be Aware:
The extended spring break is over and we all have to get to work to complete the school year. Unfortunately, due to COVID-19, we will be completing the school year from our homes, but we are going to make the best and most of it. Teachers have posted and created work for their students which is not optional, it is an expectation. In order to pass their courses students have to make sure that they are completing the work assigned from each of their teachers. Please, if you need help, don't understand something, reach out to your teachers to let them know. If you can't get a hold of your teacher, get a hold of the principal who will relay the message. Teachers are working from home and are ready and waiting to assist you in any way they can. Please know that the teachers, counselors, principals, and staff miss you all very much and we look forward to being together again, but in the mean time, let's make the most of the situation we are all in and finish the year academically strong and physically healthy.

post_text: Coach Max and Coach Gurule would like to encourage all MS/HS PE, Fitness, and Strength classes to workout on your own. Walk, jog, run at least 4 miles daily (10,000 steps goal). Check out workout videos on YouTube by Mr. Bob Harper who has great at home workouts, or use your own body weight by doing push-ups, mountain climbers, triceps dips, t-stands etc. Drink plenty of water and eat healthy snacks. Practice social distancing if you’re working out with your buddies. No more than a group of 5. Stay healthy!

ATTENTION- MS/HS STUDENTS OF JESSICA ESQUIBEL:

7th & 8th grade science students please contact Mrs. Esquibel via email jesesquibel@penascoisd.com or jesquibel@penasco.k12.nm.us , so I can give you the necessary information regarding your online science lessons.

8th grade CS Discoveries, please continue with unit 3 lessons 16-20, 30 minutes at least 4 days a week. Please make sure read instructions carefully, watch videos if required, and look at each example given. If you get frustrated then it means you’re thinking hard, give yourself a break, and then return to it. Also, please go to typing club at least once a week for 30 minutes.

9th grade CS Principals, please complete unit 3 chapter assessments, there are four assessments. Please complete these assessments this week. If you have any questions please email Mrs. Esquibel at jesesquibel@penascoisd.com, She will give you more assignments next week.

ANNOUNCING: PTO - PARENT TEACHER ORGANIZATION
All interested Parents/Guardians of Peñasco Elementary, Middle, & High School students are welcome to attend the first meeting of the Peñasco Schools PTO on Tuesday, November 5th at 6:00 pm in the Elementary Library. The meetings will continue through the rest of the school year on the 1st Tuesday of the month. We are looking forward to meeting with you!

What does a PTO do?

"The purpose of the PTO is to encourage parents to assist with various school activities/functions/services, provide financial assistance where needs are identified within the school, foster a community atmosphere, and support the mission and vision of the school and school district." (https://elmcreekpto.weebly.com/what-is-the-purpose-of-the-pto.html)

MS/HS Registration for the 2019-2020 School year will be taking place on Monday, August 5th

9:00-12:00 -12th, 11th, & 10th graders
1:00- 4:00 - 9th, 8th, 7th graders

*Remember to bring in $20 to pay for your class dues and locker fees. No Checks Accepted!

SBA (Science)- 11th graders- March 26th & 27th
NMASR (Science)- 8th grade- April 8th-11th
NMSBTA (Math & ELA) -7th - 11th grade- April 23rd- May 2nd
EoCs (End of Course Exams) 7th-12th grades- May 13-23

All students who are present and on time for testing on test days and don't have to do make-up testing will be eligible to go on the Field Trip at the end of the year.

post_text: We have only 3 short weeks, 12 school days, left before our Winter Break and there is much to accomplish to close our first semester. In the remaining weeks before our winter break Middle & High School students will be taking various assessments to include NWEA (MAPs) Short Cycle Assessment, EoCs (End of Course Exams for semester-long classes), and Final Exams in most of their classes. Attendance for the next 3 weeks is crucial. Please do all you can to make sure your child is in attendance, getting enough rest at night, and getting to school on time in the morning. The first semester and 2nd quarter end on December 20th. Remember that semester grades determine eligibility. Questions? Contact the Middle/High School office at 575-587-2502 ext 1000

Congratulations to our girls cross country team as they took 1st place at the district cross country meet! Our very own Carly Gonzales took 1st place over all.

Congratulations to our boys team who were led by Gilbert Valdez!

post_text: Tomorrow we will be hosting the cross country district meet on the Peñasco campus. Girls varsity will run at 3:30pm and boys varsity will follow at 4:00pm. Come out and support our athletes as they run to become district champions.
